    "created_at": "2014-10-07T11:57:16Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-10-07T11:57:16Z",
    "body": "In atom-shell all windows are run in separate processes, so operating the DOM of other windows would require sending synchronous messages from browser process to render process, which is very easy to result in dead locks, that's why it is not allowed.\n\nI may try to provide a simpler way for operating DOM of a window in future, but for now you have to use `BrowserWindow.executeJavaScript` explicitly.\n"
  },
